article_title: For Now, Blue Cross Brand Dominates Obamacare Exchanges

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: Health plans operating with the Blue Cross brand “captured the greatest percentage of covered lives” in 12 of 15 states in the first year private coverage was offered on exchanges under the Affordable Care Act, according to a study of market share data.
